-- LIST exhaustiveness: a match handling only the cons case must be flagged
-- at type-check time (`WHEN EMPTY THEN` is not covered). Before LIST was
-- admitted to the exhaustiveness oracle this typechecked clean and crashed
-- at eval on EMPTY with "has no corresponding pattern".
GIVEN xs IS A LIST OF NUMBER
GIVETH A NUMBER
first xs MEANS
  CONSIDER xs
  WHEN x FOLLOWED BY rest THEN x
